        <briefdescription>
<para>Legacy start tag handler. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><computeroutput>startElement</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>endElement</computeroutput> are only used by the legacy SAX1 interface and should not be used in new software. If you really have to enable SAX1, the preferred way is set the <computeroutput>initialized</computeroutput> member to 1 instead of XML_SAX2_MAGIC.</para>
<para>For backward compatibility, it&apos;s also possible to set the <computeroutput>startElementNs</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>endElementNs</computeroutput> handlers to NULL.</para>
<para>You can also set the XML_PARSE_SAX1 parser option, but versions older than 2.12.0 will probably crash if this option is provided together with custom SAX callbacks. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
